TY  - JOUR
AU  - Bouwman, Christa H. S.
T1  - Corporate Governance Propagation through Overlapping Directors
PY  - 2011
Y1  - 2011/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhr034
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 24
IS  - 7
SP  - 2358
EP  - 2394
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - How are governance practices propagated across firms? This article proposes, and empirically verifies, that observed governance practices are partly the outcome of network effects among firms with common directors. While firms attempt to select directors whose other directorships are at firms with similar governance practices (“familiarity effect”), this matching of governance practices is imperfect because other factors also affect the director choice. This generates an “influence effect” as directors acquainted with different practices at other firms influence the firm's governance to move toward the practices of those other firms. These network effects cause governance practices to converge.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhr034
ER  - 



